Raining - gray sky - no sun.  Mild SW wind.
Northwest wind- there was a lot of rain in April - I would have liked a reading right after the ice was gone 4/5/95.

Cloudy-overcast-misty-raining most of the morning.  Water is low this year.

Since the ice was out on the 10th of April- I wanted to get a water sample within two weeks of that.  Water sample was sent in on the 16th and hopefully the DNR in Madison received it by the next day- Friday.  There were very strong horizontal winds two days prior to the 16th.  The depth was only 9 feet  The lake was calm and the trees were quiet.  Temp was around 70 degrees.
light mist and then light rain in morning-ended around 2:00PM. A good soaking rain.  GRAY sky 100%.  Hardly any wind and very quiet.
gray foggy ski.  quiet with a very slight west-north west wind.
Blue sky with a tint of white.  Minimal SW  wind.  Peaceful and Quiet
cloudy- quiet- and still.  3 fishing boats
partly sunny- NW breeze.  The lake has had very little activity so far this summer.  Cottage dwellers have not been as active as in the past. I wonder if this explains the deeper secchi depths.
sw breeze.  gray sky  quiet and peaceful
sunny- hot- quiet- sounds of birds- bright sun with sprinkling of fluffy clouds
quiet NE slight breeze.  overcast with sun shining through.(it is unusual to get any wind from the E or NE)
quiet- calm-glassy lake.  blue sky and going to be hot today
lake is glassy and calm-blue sky- quiet- still and peaceful

90 degrees the past two days:  Heavy boat traffic yesterday and today:  wsw strong breeze today:  Both of these helped to push to shore grass clippings and weeds from yesterday.  It made for undesirable swimming yesterday and  today. Sky was cloudy.  Humid conditions. Red boat produced a strong wake which produced problems for some who had their boats tied to their piers.  (ropes breaking)  also the shoreline where property owners don't practice shoreline restoration.
sw breeze--light.  Blue sky.  90's the last two days.  Cooler today sw breeze--light.  Blue sky.  Once boat traffic starts-  there are bubbles all over the lake
Been cool the last few days.  Fall is in the air.  NW wind but mild
nw breeze- blue sky with with few thin clouds- crisp summer air-  quiet on this Sunday
calm- quiet- blue sky.  Peaceful- no wake.
sw gentle breeze:  after two days of heavy boat traffic
NW gentle breeze.  blue sky and quiet (peacefull)
light boat traffic this past weekend.  blue sky- calm-quiet and peaceful.  Great sunrise
the sun from the east is warm.  quiet- peaceful- not a sound. no bird noise- no nothing.
SW gentle breeze.  100% cloudy sky----over cast
w-nw wind.  sunny (blue) sky.  nice warm day.  with a slight breeze  which feels good.
blue sky  calm/quiet.   top of water is not clean.

Sunday June 11--hail- horizontal rain- and power outage.  over 10 inches of rain this month. land run-off is responsible for the low depth this early in the summer.    blue sky with clouds- warm today-  SW wind
